  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed rear dormer by reason of its height, bulk and mass would not appear suitably subservient to the scale of the existing dwelling and the cumulative impact of the existing dormer and the proposed dormer would appear as a dominant and bulky feature in the immediate area. Furthermore, the hip to gable extension, would unbalance the pair of semi-detached houses and appear as unacceptably dominant and visually intrusive harmful to the appearance of the both the host dwelling, the pair of semi-detached houses and the surrounding area contrary to Policies 7 and 26 of the Havering Local Plan and the Council's Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: Consideration was given to seeking amendments, but given conflict with adopted planning policy, it was necessary to issue a decision as close to the statutory timeframe as possible as opposed to seeking amendments which would have significantly delayed the application."
